In {{com.atlassian.jira.upgrade.tasks.util.Sequences}}, the code to determine tablename is:
{code}
      if (schemaName != null && schemaName.length() > 0 && !tableName.startsWith(schemaName))
        {
            // Prepend the schema name
            return schemaName + "." + tableName;
        }
        return tableName;
{code}

If the database schema used is {{jira}}, the returned tablename would be {{jira.jiraeventtype}} and this will cause the upgrade to fail because JIRA cannot resolve the proper tablename.

h4. Affected Databases
PostgreSQL. Other database might be affected too, as the class doesn't appear to be database-specific.

h4. Workaround
Use {{public}} as schema name as there are no JIRA tablename that starts with public.
{code:sql}
jira631=# \dt public*
No matching relations found.
jira631=# \dt jira*
                List of relations
 Schema |        Name        | Type  |   Owner
--------+--------------------+-------+-----------
 public | jiraaction         | table | atlassian
 public | jiradraftworkflows | table | atlassian
 public | jiraeventtype      | table | atlassian
 public | jiraissue          | table | atlassian
 public | jiraperms          | table | atlassian
 public | jiraworkflows      | table | atlassian
(6 rows)
{code}

